# Rover Documentation Index

## Quick Reference

### Project Overview
Rover is an AI-powered coding assistant platform that integrates Claude AI with real development environments through multi-provider sandbox orchestration.

### Key Documentation Files
- `CLAUDE.md` - Comprehensive repository information and architecture
- `README.md` - Project overview and setup instructions
- `apps/www/README.md` - Frontend application details
- `apps/broadcast/README.md` - WebSocket service documentation

### Architecture Quick Reference

#### Core Components
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15.3.3 + React 19 (`apps/www`)
- **WebSocket**: PartyKit service (`apps/broadcast`) 
- **Agent System**: Multi-provider sandboxes with Node.js daemon
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM
- **Auth**: Better Auth with GitHub OAuth

#### Key Directories
```
apps/www/src/
├── agent/           # Sandbox orchestration & Claude integration
├── components/chat/ # Real-time chat UI components
├── server-actions/  # GitHub integration & workflows
├── lib/            # Core utilities (auth, db, etc.)
└── app/            # Next.js App Router pages & API

packages/
├── shared/         # Database schemas & shared utilities
├── daemon/         # Autonomous sandbox agent
├── env/           # Environment configuration
└── r2/            # Cloudflare R2 integration
```

### Development Commands
```bash
# Start full development environment
pnpm dev

# Run tests
cd apps/www && pnpm test

# Database operations
cd apps/www && pnpm drizzle-kit-push-dev
cd apps/www && pnpm drizzle-kit-studio-dev

# Type checking
cd apps/www && pnpm check

# Deploy WebSocket service
cd apps/broadcast && pnpm deploy
```

### Technology Stack Summary

**Frontend Stack**:
- Next.js 15.3.3, React 19, Tailwind CSS v4
- Jotai, TanStack React Query, Radix UI + shadcn/ui

**Backend Stack**:
- Drizzle ORM, Better Auth, Hono, tRPC
- Anthropic Claude SDK, E2B, CodeSandbox APIs

**Infrastructure**:
- PostgreSQL, Redis (Upstash), Cloudflare R2
- PartyKit (WebSocket), Vercel (hosting)

### Key Features
- Multi-provider sandbox environments (E2B, CodeSandbox)
- Real-time collaborative coding with Claude AI
- Automated GitHub workflows (commits, PRs)
- Resource management with hibernation
- Mobile-responsive design

### Important Patterns
- Use workspace packages (`@rover/*`) for shared code
- Follow established component patterns in `src/components/`
- Implement proper error handling and loading states
- Use TypeScript interfaces with strict typing
- Leverage server components where possible